{
  "texts": [
    "If the nodes V cyc,̸ =0 were sampled uniformly, then |V fst,̸ =0 | would be of the order of a|V cyc,̸ =0 |.",
    "However, the number of fasteners in V fst,̸ =0 can be much smaller for unfavorable configurations such that fastener nodes are in the same community as v 1 or v 2.",
    "Nevertheless, if this happens, then the number of boundary edges in E ↑ cyc,0 must be high accordingly to compensate this drop in the number of fasteners in V fst,̸ =0.",
    "Let us explain how Proposition 3.1 follows from Lemmas 3.1 and 4.1.",
    "First, we observe that an edge between two communities is either a fastener edge and is therefore incident to V fst,̸ =0 or is a cycle edge and therefore both arises in E ↑ cyc,k and E ↑ cyc,k ′ for k ̸ = k ′ being the two communities to which the nodes of the edge belong."
  ]
}